```json
{
  "application": "MLPerf",
  "details": {
    "framework": "pytorch",
    "model": "recommendation",
    "ruleset": "3.0.0",
    "container": "${CONT}",
    "data_dir": "${DATADIR}",
    "data_val_dir": "${DATADIR_VAL}",
    "api_log_dir": "${API_LOG_DIR}",
    "log_dir": "${LOGDIR}",
    "power_command_dir": "${POWERCMDDIR}",
    "num_experiments": "${NEXP}",
    "clear_caches": "${CLEAR_CACHES}",
    "check_compliance": "${CHECK_COMPLIANCE}",
    "mounts": "${MOUNTS}"
  },
  "resources": {
    "compute": {
      "nodes": "${SLURM_JOB_NUM_NODES}",
      "tasks_per_node": 1,
      "mpi": "${SLURM_MPI_TYPE:-pmix}"
    },
    "storage": {
      "data_dir": "${DATADIR}",
      "data_val_dir": "${DATADIR_VAL}",
      "api_log_dir": "${API_LOG_DIR}",
      "log_dir": "${LOGDIR}"
    }
  }
}
```

This script is running an MLPerf benchmark for a recommendation model using PyTorch. It includes details about the container image, data directories, API logging, results logging, and power measurement commands. The script also specifies resource requirements, including the number of nodes, tasks per node, and the MPI type. The script also uses several environment variables to configure the experiment, including the DGX system, the container image, and the data directory.
